    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained rice</strong> with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[400ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low until very gently bubbling and cook, covered, for 15 min</p><p>After 15 min, remove the pot from the heat and keep covered for a further 10 min before serving</p><p>Tip: Don't peek! Keep the lid on the whole time to get fluffy and sticky rice!</p>",
      "order": 3,
