    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the juice of your <strong>orange[s] </strong>in a bowl with your <strong>cornflour</strong>,<strong> </strong>then add your<strong> soy sauce</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong>,<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 50ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>ponzu-style sauce</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>ponzu-style sauce </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened to a syrup-like consistency, then set aside to cool – this is your <strong>ponzu-style glaze</strong></p>",
